title: Looking for a modern yet vintage logo for my new physical therapy clinic!

The idea to establish Focus Rehabilitation came about after burn out started to set in and care declined as a result of corporate companies placing shareholders' interests over quality of care. Patients are starting to believe it is normal to be treated at the same time other individuals are receiving care by the same provider. As a result, valued patients view physical therapy services as a waste of their time and money.
Focus Rehabilitation is built on being community oriented and delivering individualized 1-on-1 care to all patients in order to gain respect and also achieve optimal level of function. The clinic will be located in Red Bud, IL, a small, rural town in Southern IL. It is our mission for every patient to experience the same small town feeling compassion and treatment each time they walk into our doors.
My husband and I are the sole owners of the company. Believing God has blessed us with the opportunity of starting this company and allowing us to provide care to our community, we would like to incorporate faith into our logo. We had the idea of subtly including a cross out of the f of Focus and also really emphasizing the U to illustrate the focus on our patients. The clinic will exist in an old brick building built in 1860s at the heart of the town and therefore we have the vision of a more vintage logo as well. We plan to incorporate neutral colors, such as navy, burgundy and olive green, in the interior and exterior of the building.
Services provided: Outpatient physical therapy
Target population: general public
